title: Australia sharks: Campaigners call for end to nets
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Australia sharks: Campaigners call for end to nets 1 February 2017 Last updated at 02:28 GMT 
In Australia, campaigners are calling for an end to the use of shark nets at beaches, because they are killing dolphins and turtles. 
More have been installed after a recent spate of shark attacks on the east coast - but some nets have been cut deliberately by those who oppose them. Read more
